I"U<p>These days I was learning German grammar of transforming adjective. I learnt so many rules like,  when the non which you describe is a accusative, if it’s male word append <code class="highlighter-rouge">en</code>, if it’s female or plural append <code class="highlighter-rouge">e</code>, if it’s neutral append <code class="highlighter-rouge">es</code>. But when the article is <code class="highlighter-rouge">meine</code> or <code class="highlighter-rouge">keine</code> and the word is plural, append <code class="highlighter-rouge">en</code> For nominative and dative phrase …..</p>
